    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, who leads the squad with an 81.88 efficiency score against Wacha. The combination of an elite batting order spot and favorable park factors makes him our primary engine for R and HR today. **Kyle Tucker** (78.04) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (75.48) round out the top tier of the outfield; **Kyle Tucker** benefits from strong xwOBA metrics, while **Luis Robert Jr.** exploits a significant dynamic platoon advantage against Prielipp. Additionally, **Jackson Merrill** is a high-value play at 75.27, bolstered significantly by a +14% park factor, making him a critical component for driving production in the middle of our order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, whose 58.68 score narrowly missed the cut behind **Marcell Ozuna** and **Andy Pages**. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** maintains a strong 0.384 xwOBA, his efficiency is currently depressed by a negative dynamic platoon adjustment against Soriano, leading us to favor the higher-percentage matchups provided by the active starters. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** presents as a sneaky upside play today (73.66); his matchup against Fuentes is highly advantageous, with an impressive +19% boost from the opposing pitcher\u2019s skill level and a robust +14% platoon edge. We are keeping a close watch on **Liam Hicks** (44.89), who occupies the lowest efficiency slot in our starting lineup; while he serves his purpose, he remains the primary candidate to be swapped should we need to elevate a bench asset like **Josh Jung** or **Coby Mayo** if late-breaking lineup news shifts the projections.",
